<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#F0DCA0">Originally posted by Moriendor on 05-04-2002 01:34 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Whoops, sorry about the double post but I didn't notice that this is the "demo opinion" thread when I replied to Al's post  :) .

Anyway, here's some more notes:

1) A save game description would be very nice. There could be a default description like "Aleroth - Day 1, 01:30 hours". Would be even better if you could edit that description to your own liking. The "01:30" should be the time the player has been into the game. Would be cool if you were able to track how much time you spent in  :div: in total.

2) An automatic selection of the last save would be nice when you access the "Load game" menu. Right now, you have to select the game you want to load. Would make life easier if the last save game was set as the default load option.

3) It says "3th Day" in the diary. Should be changed to "3rd". Minor typo.

4) Why doesn't the mouse wheel work in trade mode?

5) It seems like you can't tell whether you sell items that you are currently wearing on person or items in your inventory. I may have overlooked something here but I sold a tunic that my char was wearing. Had another one in my inventory but my char didn't auto-equip the one from my backpack. Could become dangerous and tedious to check if you sold from your inventory or from your currently equipped items.

6) When you play as a warrior it would be cool if the 'Way of the Warrior' would be displayed as the default page when you hit the "Skills" button (in the demo, the 'Way of the Wizard/Mage' is shown first). Same goes for wizard and survivor, of course. Just display the way fitting to the char after the player hits the "Skills" button.

That's it for today. More to come  ;) .

------------------
Moriendor
Editor @ [URL=http://www.rpgdot.com/]RPGDot[/URL]
Webmaster @ [URL=http://www.divinity-the-sword-of-lies.com]Divinity-The-Sword-Of-Lies.com[/URL]</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
